HEADWORD: Transliteration
<hw>Trans*lit`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
product of transliterating, or of expressing words of a language by
means of the characters of another alphabet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

